# 5. できることを精一杯

Honami: Oh wow! Look at all the wedding dresses...!
Mizuki: Whoa! Check out that ball gown! It looks so fluffy!
Mizuki: No sleeves either! It's simple and really pretty! Oh, this mini skirt's also super cute!
Mizuki: We can seriously choose from any of these dresses?!
Emu: Yup! Pick whichever you like! The staff here will answer any questions you have☆
Mizuki: Cool! Then, where to start... Maybe something standard, like an A-line...
Emu: Oh, those are over that way! I'll show you!
Honami: Those two certainly seem to be enjoying themselves. Which would you like to try on, Ms. Yoisaki?
Kanade: I'm not sure... I don't even know where to begin, so I'm okay with just seeing what's here.
Honami: Oh, I see...
Honami: But wouldn't you like to try one on since we're here? It might be a good change of pace to put on something that you don't normally wear.
Honami: Why don't we try picking something out together? If you tell me your preferences, we may be able to find one you like.
Kanade: I see... Then, if you don't mind.
Honami: Of course. Let's find one together.
Kanade: I was initially under the impression that wedding dresses all had to be white. But the dress exhibit showed me how they come in a variety of colors, and I see the same thing here.
Honami: White is the old standard, but there's actually nothing wrong with choosing another color. What do you like, Ms. Yoisaki...?
Kanade: Well, I'm not set on any particular one, but something simple and subdued might be nice if I'm going to be wearing it. I'd feel pretty embarrassed if I ended up standing out by wearing something too vivid...
Honami: Then, one of these may work... This one has a bit of light gray mixed in. Yes, I think this would look really good on you.
Honami: Or... Oh, how about this one? The lace pattern on it is so beautiful.
Kanade: Okay, I think I'll try this one. Thank you for helping me choose, Ms. Mochizuki.
Honami: I'm glad we were able to find something you like.
Kanade: Me too. Oh, but... Ms. Mochizuki, you haven't picked a dress yet.
Honami: Don't mind me. It shouldn't take me too long to pick one.
Kanade: Okay...
Kanade: I'm sorry...
Honami: Huh? Why are you apologizing?
Kanade: I feel like I've been giving you things to worry about this entire day.
Kanade: Not only did you go out of your way to invite me to this event, you just helped me pick out a dress to wear...
Kanade: Even when we were going around the booth area, you noticed that I was tired and suggested that we go somewhere with less people.
Honami: I-I'm sorry. I must've seemed too overbearing.
Kanade: No, please, don't say that. If anything, I'm glad you're so worried about me.
Kanade: It's just... I feel like I'm making you work even though you're technically off right now.
Kanade: I know this isn't normal. So, I'm sorry...
Honami: No, I... I like doing this is all.
Honami: So, please don't mind me. As long as you have fun today, I'll be happy.
Kanade: Ms. Mochizuki...
Kanade: Then, I will... Thank you...
Honami: (I just wanted Ms. Yoisaki to enjoy herself, but that ended up having the opposite effect...)
Honami: (This is so much more difficult than I realized...)
Mizuki: Hey! Have you two picked out your dresses yet?
Emu: Wow, Kanade, is that what you're gonna wear?! It's so pretty!
Kanade: Ms. Mochizuki helped me choose it. Otori, Mizuki, have you already picked yours out?
Emu: Yup☆ I just found the one I wanna wear!
Mizuki: I'm still kinda torn... Can I ask you all for your opinions?
Kanade: Sure. Oh, but... Ms. Mochizuki still needs a dress.
Mizuki: Oh, okay. Then, Honami, you should probably go find one for yourself!
Emu: Oh, I'll go with her! Kanade, you help Mizuki pick a dress☆
Kanade: Okay, but I don't know if my opinion will help...
Mizuki: Don't worry! Just say whatever comes to mind for me!
Emu: Honami, they have lots and lots of pretty dresses here, so I'll try to show you as many of them as I can!
Honami: Hehe. I really appreciate it, Emu.
Emu: Hmm... Honami! Honami! How about this one?
Honami: Oh! What a pretty pink, like the color of cherry blossoms... It's so lovely!
Emu: Hehe. I'm glad you like it! I thought it'd look really great on you! Also, just gimme a second to bring over some of the dresses I saw in that other section!
Honami: Hehe. Thank you, Emu.
Emu: ...
Emu: Is something wrong, Honami? You're all bunched up like a scrunchie...
Honami: L-Like a scrunchie...?
Emu: Oh, I mean... You look like you're thinking a whole lot and your heart's being squeezed really tight!
Emu: At least, that's the expression you had on your face just now...
Honami: Oh...
Emu: Is something bothering you? If so, you can tell me!
Honami: Thank you, Emu.
Honami: Then, if you don't mind listening...
Emu: So, you just want Kanade to have fun today...?
Honami: Yes, that was the plan. But it sort of ended up having the opposite effect.
Honami: I didn't realize it would be this difficult...
Emu: Hmm... Isn't there anything we can do...?
Emu: Oh, I know!
Emu: When I think “fun”, I think “shows”☆ So, we should put one on together!
Honami: Us? Putting a show...?
Emu: Heh heh heh! Just leave it to me! I've got a great idea♪
Mizuki: Ta-daa! Check it out, everyone! This is the dress I chose!
Honami: Wow, so many frills...! It's adorable!
Mizuki: I know, right? It's a pretty simple design outside of the frills, but that means it shouldn't take too much time or effort to put on. I figure I can try on a bunch of different dresses if they're like this!
Mizuki: But I was really torn between pastel pink and magenta... Luckily, Kanade told me what she thought and I was able to decide on the pastel one!
Honami: Hehe. I think it's going to look really good on you, Mizuki.
Mizuki: Hehe. Thanks! Do you already know what you're gonna wear, Honami?
Honami: Yes, Emu helped me with that.
Mizuki: Great. Then, let's head to the fitting rooms!
Emu: Oh, Mizuki! Before we do!
Emu: Did you know that you can do something really fun here along with trying on wedding dresses...?
Kanade: Something fun...?
Emu: Yeah! After you pick out a dress, guess what...?!
Emu: You can have your own mock wedding!!!
Mizuki: A mock wedding...? Yeah, that does sound like a lot of fun!
Emu: Hehe. Doesn't it? You can have your pictures taken and even have a flower shower like a real wedding!
Emu: And there's more!
Emu: It doesn't have to be just any old wedding... It can also be a show that you take part in!
Kanade: A show?
Emu: Yeah, with the two participants as the main characters!
Emu: My brothers asked me if there was some way to make things more enjoyable for the guests...
Emu: So, I had a brainstorming session with Tsukasa, Nene, and Rui, and we came up with...!
Emu: “A Beleaguered Bride: A Special Wedding Presentation”!
Kanade: What? A beleaguered bride...?
Mizuki: If it's something Rui and Tsukasa came up with, it's probably gonna be a bit nuts...
Honami: Haha. True...
Kanade: But being in a show sounds difficult. Are you sure it's okay for complete amateurs to participate...?
Emu: Don't worry! Anyone is free to join in because it's such a simple story! You don't even have to read a script! Just listen to what the staff say and do what you'd do normally!
Emu: Shows are really fun to watch, but they're just as fun to be a part of! I spent a lot of time with Tsukasa and the others thinking about how to make this fun for all the guests!
Mizuki: Really...? Then, should we give it a shot? I mean, it does sound pretty fun!
Honami: Umm...
Honami: (Yes, we shouldn't have much trouble participating in this show...)
Honami: (But I hardly ever do anything like this, so I'm a little worried as to how I'll do...)
Honami: (At the same time, if this is a chance for Ms. Yoisaki to have more fun...)
Honami: I-I'd like to give it a try...!
Kanade: R-Really...?
Honami: Y-Yes! I think it'll be fun! So... Ms. Yoisaki, would you like to be in it as well?
Kanade: But I've never been in a show like this before...
Mizuki: I think we're all in the same boat there. Why not take this opportunity to be in one with her, Kanade?
Mizuki: I really wanna see you perform in it while wearing that dress you picked out♪
Kanade: M-Mizuki...
Mizuki: Haha! But I won't force you to do anything you don't want to.
Mizuki: Still, this kind of chance doesn't come by that often, so I kinda want you to have as much fun as possible.
Kanade: Oh...
Honami: Wh-What do you say, Ms. Yoisaki? Would you like to join me...?
Kanade: Okay, I'll do it...
Emu: You will?! Woohoo!
Emu: Then, I'll go let the staff know☆ Honami, Kanade, you two get changed!
Honami: Okay! Thank you, Emu!
Mizuki: Hehe. I can't wait to see your guys' show! And you wearing your dresses!
Mizuki: So, Kanade, Honami, break a leg!
Kanade: O-Okay...
Honami: (I have to do my absolute best in order to make sure Ms. Yoisaki enjoys herself...!)
